omprehensive Bibliography -- tContributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aPioneering participatory, social change-oriented media, the program had a national and international impact on documentary film-making, yet this is the first comprehensive history and analysis of its work. The volume's contributors study dozens of films produced by the program, their themes, aesthetics, and politics, and evaluate their legacy and the program's place in Canadian, Québécois, and world cinema. An informative and nuanced look at a cinematic movement, Challenge for Change reemphasizes not just the importance of the NFB and its programs but also the role documentaries can play in improving the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDocumentary filmszCanadaxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh1 aAngelico, Irene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaker, Michael Brendan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBaker, Michael Brendan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanning, Kass, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyle, Deirdre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCammaer, Gerda Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharbonneau, Stephen Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCizek, Katerina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorneil, Marit Kathryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCzach, Liz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDansereau, Fernand, econtributor.4ctb4https://id